ğŸ«€ CardioPredict: Heart Failure Risk Assessment

A lightweight machine learning application to predict patient mortality risk based on clinical parameters.

ğŸ“ Description

CardioPredict is a machine learning project designed to assess the risk of death (mortality) in heart failure patients using a set of common clinical features. The core of the project is a Random Forest Classifier trained on high-quality clinical records. It solves the problem of rapid risk stratification in a clinical context, offering a quick, data-driven perspective on a patient's prognosis. The target audience includes medical researchers, data scientists, and healthcare professionals interested in predictive modeling for cardiovascular health.

âœ¨ Features

High Accuracy: Achieves an accuracy of approximately 85% on the held-out test set for binary classification (survival vs. mortality).

Feature Scaling: Uses StandardScaler to normalize numerical input features, ensuring robust model training.

Robust Model: Implements a Random Forest Classifier, known for its good performance, feature importance ranking, and resistance to overfitting.

Interactive CLI: Provides a simple command-line interface for entering patient data and receiving real-time predictions.

Clear Data Handling: Demonstrates complete data loading, splitting, scaling, training, and evaluation workflows.

